objectives:

    The focus of this course in on the study of the concept of 'Property', the 'nature of property rights' and the general principles governing the transfer of property. A detailed study of the substantive law relating to particular transfers, such as sale, mortgage, lease, exchange, gift and actionable claims will also be undertaken. The course also includes an exposure into the concept of trust.

unit 1:
    General principles of Transfer of Property by act of parties inter- vivos- Concept and meaning of immovable property- Transfer of Immovable Property- Persons Competent to transfer - Operation of Transfer- Conditions restraining alienation and restrictions repugnant to the interest created- rule against perpetuity and exceptions- Direction for accumulation- Vested and Contingent interest, void conditions, Rule of acceleration, fulfillment of conditions subsequent.

unit 2:
    Doctrine of election- transfer by ostensible and co-owner- Apportionment- Priority of rights-Rent paid to holder under defective title- Improvements made by bonafide holder- Doctrine of Lis pendens- Fraudulent transfer and part-performance.

unit 3:
    Mortgages of Immovable property: Definition- Kinds of mortgages and their features- Rights and liabilities of mortgagor and mortgagee- Priority of securities- Marshalling and contribution-Charges.

unit 4:
    Sale of immovable property: Rights and liabilities of seller and buyer before and after completion of sale- Difference between sale and contract for sale: Leases of immovable property: Definition- Scope- creation of lease- rights and liabilities of lessor and lessee-Determination and holding over; Exchange: Definition and mode- Actionable Claims; Gifts: Scope- meaning- mode of transfer- universal gifts- onerous gifts.

unit 5:
    Law of Trusts with Fiduciary Relations: Definitions of Trust and its comparison with other relationships like Debt, Ownership, Bailment, Agency and Contract; Kinds of Trusts- Creation of Trust- Appointment of Trustees- Duties and Liabilities of Trustees- Rights and Powers of Trustees- Disabilities of Trustee- Rights and Liabilities of the Beneficiary- Vacating the office of trustee and Extinction of Trusts.

books prescribed:
    Mulla, Transfer of Property Act,(Delhi: Universal, 1999)
    Tandon, M.P., Indian Trust Act,1882, 21st Edition, (Allahabad Law Agency, 2012)

reference books:
    Subbarao, Transfer of Property,(Madras: Subbiah Chetty, 1994)
    Shukla, S.N, Transfer of Property Act, 28th Edition, (Jain Book Agency, 2014 )
    Tripathi, G.P., The Transfer of Property Act, 18th Edition, (Jain Book Agency, 2014)


questions:

    Unit 1 - General Principles of Transfer of Property

        Explain the concept and meaning of immovable property under the Transfer of Property Act. Discuss the general principles governing transfer of property by act of parties inter-vivos with relevant case laws.

        Examine the provisions relating to persons competent to transfer property. Discuss the operation of transfer and conditions restraining alienation and restrictions repugnant to the interest created.

        Critically analyse the rule against perpetuity and its exceptions. Discuss the concepts of vested and contingent interest, void conditions, rule of acceleration and fulfillment of conditions subsequent with relevant judicial pronouncements.

    Unit 2 - Doctrines and Special Provisions

        Explain the doctrine of election and discuss transfer by ostensible and co-owner. Examine the concept of apportionment and priority of rights with relevant case laws.

        Discuss the provisions relating to rent paid to holder under defective title and improvements made by bonafide holder. Explain the doctrine of Lis pendens with leading judicial pronouncements.

        Critically analyse the provisions relating to fraudulent transfer and part-performance under the Transfer of Property Act. Discuss the protection available to bonafide transferees with relevant case laws.

    Unit 3 - Mortgages of Immovable Property

        Define mortgage and explain different kinds of mortgages and their features under the Transfer of Property Act. Discuss the rights and liabilities of mortgagor and mortgagee with relevant case laws.

        Examine the provisions relating to priority of securities under the Transfer of Property Act. Discuss the concepts of marshalling and contribution with leading judicial interpretations.

        Critically analyse the provisions relating to charges under the Transfer of Property Act. Distinguish between mortgage and charge with relevant judicial pronouncements.

    Unit 4 - Sale, Lease, Exchange and Gifts

        Discuss the rights and liabilities of seller and buyer before and after completion of sale under the Transfer of Property Act. Distinguish between sale and contract for sale with relevant case laws.

        Examine the provisions relating to lease of immovable property under the Transfer of Property Act. Discuss the rights and liabilities of lessor and lessee, and provisions relating to determination and holding over.

        Explain the provisions relating to exchange, actionable claims and gifts under the Transfer of Property Act. Discuss the scope, mode of transfer and special features with relevant judicial interpretations.

    Unit 5 - Law of Trusts

        Define trust and distinguish it from other relationships like debt, ownership, bailment, agency and contract. Discuss the different kinds of trusts with relevant case laws.

        Examine the provisions relating to creation of trust and appointment of trustees under the Indian Trusts Act. Discuss the duties, liabilities, rights and powers of trustees with leading judicial pronouncements.

        Critically analyse the provisions relating to rights and liabilities of beneficiaries under the Indian Trusts Act. Discuss the disabilities of trustees, vacating the office of trustee and extinction of trusts with relevant case laws.
